metadata.name: The Spectrum Of Nature #139
metadata.description:
*\_../*`¬-’\/*`¬’’¬`*\/’-¬`*\.._/*

Nature, nature, evolving might… Silent inventor, always right.
Where is the edge of nature and where do we begin?  
What is of nature and what is of man? 
Isn't everything made by nature's hands?

To know more about the concept and technicalities of this piece, see the fxtext article “The spectrum of nature - a short making of”. Link at the bottom. If you’d rather just ignore my personal meaning, feel free to skip the article. 

\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\

Basic info:
The piece comes in possible portrait or landscape versions. Both have a relative size of 1 by 1.5. So the initial render will be 1000px wide and 1500px high for portrait. And 1500x1000 for landscape. With the ability to scale this up (see below).

The piece uses WebGL, so will perform much better with a graphics card. A faster computer will obviously be better, though I've done my very best to make it fast and efficient for any old laptop. My hope is that you will find the render process quick and enjoyable for the amount of detail that’s present. 

../’`*’`\../’`*’`\../’`*’`\../’`*’`\../’`*’`\..

Controls:
Press the [s] key to save the initial render. You will need to wait a few seconds after all the elements have stopped loading. A box will pop up in the top left saying “done” for 4 seconds when it’s ready. For the [s] key to work you may need to open in a new tab. But can right click save otherwise.

Larger sizes:
Press the [2-9] keys to save a resolution of that key size. So [2] saves a 2000x3000 size image, [9] saves a 9000x13500 size image etc. Unless you are making some very large prints you probably won’t need more than 4k (even 2-3k is big). Though the option is there. 

There may be slight variations in the textures for the larger renders, this is because the shader code has to redraw the textures at the higher pixel resolution, and getting the textures where they sit is more of an art than a science. All the elements remain exact however. 

/*/*/*/*/*/*/*/*/*/*/*/*/*/*/*/*/*/*

Made with javascript and some small extra code:
A palette creator by @nathansonic
Noisejs - github.com/josephg/noisejs - Perlin noise generator
Twgl - github.com/greggman/twgl.js - A small webGL helper.

metadata.name: the boxes we live in #167
metadata.description:
Throughout our lives we are placed in boxes that define who we are and limit how we think of ourselves. 

I am a father, husband, son, brother, friend. I am an artist, programmer, photographer, musician, designer, creator. I am a student and I am a teacher. I am a good person. I am a bad person. I am a human.

What boxes do you put yourself in, and do you let others put you in? Is it possible to break out of the boxes that define your life? Do you even want to? What's outside of these boundaries? What is at the center?

metadata.name: Florescence #289
metadata.description:
Digitally crafted flowers in pots for virtual window sills.

In the spirit of the piranha plant from the Mario Bros videogame. We wanted to create a project that acknowledges the playful depiction of nature in early videogames by creating a retro futuristic collectible that explores aesthetics over gameplay, whilst preserving the playful energy of these early digital worlds. There are many game elements that have emerged over the years that have become iconic in their own right. Their memorable designs have come to represent the exciting feeling of when we first discovered these worlds, but over time an appreciation for their simple design execution, harmony and balance has emerged. Art can exist in many forms and places including a digital pot plant.

Rarity:

There are a total of 23 hand-drawn and animated sprites divided into 4 groups Firelillies, Flytraps, Quasars and Stargazers and there are 15 possible combinations made from these 4 groups. 18% of the collection is a combination of these 4 groups which we can call random and the remaining 72% is divided between the remaining 14 combinations.


There are 3 possible grid systems 1x1, 3x3 and 4x4 

3% 1x1

40% 3x3

57% 4x4



There are 14 possible placement points for all grids and 76 stem/sprite arragement in total



For the pots and stems there are 11 colors to choose and  no rarities for color combinations.



The flower distribution can be either symmetric or random. 35% symmetric and 65% random



Export options:

Pressing 's' on desktop or holding for 2 seconds will download gif to whatever the current device resolution is. To export at a different resolution open the token in new window by clicking 'open' link under the token image and add "&exportsize=1080" or "&exportsize=2160" to end of the url and hit enter then either hold for 2 seconds or press 's' to create gif and download.

metadata.description:
Цвет (Eng.: Colour) is the 4th and last collection of my Suprematic series.
Colours have escaped the shapes, transcended into the infinite space.

Press [1…6] to change the image resolution up to 10k.
Press [P] to pause.

metadata.name: Rite of Passage #179
metadata.description:
In life, we all take different paths, different rites of passage, and while the end is all that's ever true, we will still all view it and experience it in very different ways, like that masterpiece hanging on the wall at the end of our gallery visit. 
  

There are always things that we will never have the power to change, but at the same time, we determine the route, we influence the journey, we can choose the person we want to be. We'll look back on memories, we'll have regrets, and we'll think about what could have been - but unlike this artwork, in the end we won't be able to change the final output by simply pressing a number - so live well and be happy my friends. 

---------------------

Generative artwork by Sykcolo / @sykcoloart

Primary sale proceeds:
50% to Processing Foundation
50% to Savepakistan

Royalties:
50% to the original minter
50% to artist (me)

Press '2' to '4' to see what could have been + increase pixel density. 
Press 's' to save

Details:

150 hand-picked colour pallets (thanks to @SteveMakerspace for colour selection method)
2 Frame types
4 Art types
2 Times of day (light or dark background)

License: MIT

Happy Birthday fxhash

metadata.name: We Are Alone Together #495
metadata.description:
We meander through the flows of life, alone but together. This experience — an ultimately solitary one — is communicated but never truly shared. Our consciousnesses live in a perpetual separated state, alone but together.

############

Display resolution scales with window size. Press ’h’ (in live mode) to generate a 6000x7500 hi-res image. This may take a few seconds to generate depending on your hardware. Press ‘d’ to redraw the artwork.

Original artwork by perkwerk * made with p5.js * 2022
